    "body": "> Are there any workarounds here, or is the limitation the nodes themselves, and the amount of data they have to fetch?\r\n\r\nAnother way of speeding up forking is to reduce the distance (like, the physical distance) to the node you're forking from. This means either having a node running in your LAN, or running your code \"closer to the remote node\", if that's possible at all. For example, I'm in the southern hemisphere, so running our forking tests in my machine against Alchemy takes way longer than doing the same in GithHub's CI, which is surely much closer to wherever Alchemy's nodes are located.",
